==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spiry
<hw>Spir"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Spire</er> a
winding line.]</ety> <def>Of a spiral form; wreathed; curled;
serpentine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hid in the <qex>spiry</qex> volumes of the snake.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spiry</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spiry
<hw>Spir"y</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[FR. <er>Spire</er> a
steeple.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a spire; like a spire, tall,
slender, and tapering; abounding in spires; <as>as, <ex>spiry</ex>
turrets</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Spiry</xex> towns.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spiss</ent>⟦br⟧
